RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 85. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000, For Each $5,000 To $40,000 2 lbs. (Rail at 18 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADELIE (IRE) brushed leaving the gate, traveled two wide near the back, swung out leaving the far turn and came four wide into the stretch, rallied from outside, dueled with HAPPYASACLAM (IRE) late and bested the runner-up. HAPPYASACLAM (IRE) tracked the pace from inside, steered out to the three path on the far turn, drew alongside the leader at the eighth pole, gained the advantage midstretch, dueled with ADELIE (IRE) in the final sixteenth and got outkicked. PRINCESS MIDNIGHT bumped with inner rival at the start, cleared and angled across to the inside, set all the pace to the stretch, put to left handed urging and was tested in upper stretch, lost command approaching the sixteenth pole, yielded to the top pair and stayed on to secure the show. VIEWERS DISCRETION got bumped on both sides at the start, raced three wide into the clubhouse turn then angled to the rail around the bend, made progress up the inside but had to pause when boxed in on the far turn, tipped out at the top of the lane, came back in some and kept trying late but was unable to get by PRINCESS MIDNIGHT for third. INVENTING ANNA broke well then took a stalking position next to the fence, patiently ridden through the far turn, roused into the lane and weakened. MONIQUE brushed at the start, rated while keen early in the two path outside a rival, coaxed along on the far turn, chased between into the drive, bothered by outer rival midstretch but was already starting to weaken. STORMING GRAY got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, tracked in the three path to the far turn, dropped back on the second bend, trailed two wide into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Adelie (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Abbondanza Racing LLC and Aldabbagh Omar

ENTRY.NAME: Inventing Anna
ENTRY.OWNER: J and J Stables LLC It's All About The Girls Stable LLC and Gasaway Sharilyn

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Desi Arnaz S. DEL MAR RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 94. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES, TWO YEARS OLD. By subscription of $100 each to accompany the nomination Closed Thursday November 9,2023 with 9 or by supplementary nomination of $1,000 each by closing time of entries, closed with 1 (Halone) $1,500 additional to start, with $ 100,000 Guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. Weight 124 lbs. Non-winners of a sweepstakes of $60,000* allowed 2 lbs.; of two races other than claiming or starter, 4 lbs. Non- winners of a race other than claiming, 6 lbs. High weights preferred. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. Total non-claiming earnings will be used in determining the preference of horses assigned equal weights. A tr ophy will be presented to the winning owner. *$60,000 to the winner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOTHING LIKE YOU chased along the rail into the turn, came under a ride on the turn, entered the lane two wide, drifted out past the eighth pole, surged late and got up at the wire. TAMBO closest in pursuit of ROYAL SLIPPER up the backstretch, challenged from outside at the five-sixteenths pole, took over in upper stretch, put away inner rival midstretch, drifted out late meeting the bid from NOTHING LIKE YOU and got nailed on the line. ROYAL SLIPPER away quickly from the gate to clear the field, controlled the pace up the backstretch, met the bid from TAMBO at the five-sixteenths pole, dueled into the lane, lost command in upper stretch, faltered in the furlong grounds and churned on for a clear third. DON'T BRING CRAZY chased three wide into the turn, inched closer around the bend, came four wide into the stretch and flattened out. HALONE hit the gate and came away a bit slow, trailed well off the rail early on, rounded the bend four then five wide and was not persevered with in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: Hunt Georgia Antley Giglio Jeff and Rogitz John L

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 92. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 18 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEON LIGHTS (IRE) sprinted to the front and moved across to the inside, pressured leaving the backstretch, cleared again on the turn and held well under a drive. VEGAS BURNER forwardly placed from inside, saved ground through the turn, remained on the fence through the lane and got up for second. PETCOFF came in and caused a chain reaction between rivals early, went up to press the pace at the seven-sixteenths pole, could not keep the pressure on through the turn, chased two wide into the drive, finished willingly but got edged for second at the wire. JOHNNY DRAMA bumped in the beginning, got bumped around between rivals and crowded shortly after, chased two then three wide on the turn and lacked a rally. CLASSICAL bumped hard with MOBE TOWN early, chased between then two wide on the turn and weakened. MOBE TOWN got bumped on both sides and checked early, saved ground through the turn, lacked room and put the brakes on again at the top of the lane and lacked a rally. ANNIVERSAIRE D'OR broke in and bumped rival, got forced into inner rival and checked early, raced in range three wide through the bend and weakened down the lane. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED PETCOFF FROM THIRD TO LAST FOR SHIFTING IN AND CAUSING A CHAIN REACTION BETWEEN SEVERAL RIVALS EARLY IN THE RACE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000, For Each $5,000 To $40,000 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASIAN MATRIARCH vied between rivals around the first turn, pressed the pace up the backstretch, headed the leader again on the far turn, took over past the quarter pole, led three wide into the stretch, dueled with SHE'S MY NIECE in the final furlong and gamely prevailed. SHE'S MY NIECE vied three deep into the first turn then ceded command to inner rivals, stalked up the backstretch, continued three wide into the second bend, bid three deep with a quarter mile remaining, dueled outside ASIAN MATRIARCH in the furlong grounds and lacked the needed late punch to go by. BOSSY BRUIN GAL vied along the rail with outer rivals before inching ahead on the first turn, set the pace with ASIAN MATRIARCH in the middle stages, headed again on the second bend, relinquished the lead past the quarter pole and weakened down the lane. HIGH FLYING GRACIE chased two wide then moved inside on the clubhouse turn, lost ground around the far turn and came up empty in the lane. SUPER ENTICING trailed on the inside into the first turn and dropped back, continued to lose ground on the backstretch, eased into the far turn, pulled up midway around the bend and walked off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed inside, eased, pulled up 2nd, walked off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 96. Claiming Purse 47000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since August 18 Allowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARKS HIP stepped to the front and moved to the rail, controlled the pace to the quarter pole, given his cue at the top of the lane, put to the left hand shortly after and held safely to the wire. FOR A LAUGH (IRE) tracked two wide then moved inside, angled out past the quarter pole, altered out around troubled pair in upper stretch and finished well to gain second. TOM AND JAZZY pulled early along the inside then settled into a stride stalking the leader, coaxed along through the second bend and tipped two wide at the quarter pole, shifted out for room in upper stretch but bumped LOW EXPECTATIONS in the process and finished evenly in the late stages. SYNTACTIC unhurried in the beginning and tucked inside at the back, saved ground through the far turn, steered out in upper stretch, passed a pair of rivals but failed to threaten. KID AZTECA chased in the three path on the clubhouse turn, continued three wide into the second bend, moved down to the two path before angling four wide into the drive and lacked the needed response. LOW EXPECTATIONS stalked in the two path outside a rival, got moved out to the three path at the quarter pole, knocked off strides briefly by inner rival in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAY ON THE FENCE bumped inner rival at the start, stalked along the rail into the turn, tipped out and challenged the leaders at the quarter pole, cleared three wide into the lane, drifted in past the sixteenth pole and stayed clear to the wire. J DUTTON bumped leaving the gate, vied for command inside rivals, cleared briefly on the turn before being confronted by the winner at the quarter pole, relinquished the lead shortly after, stayed on from inside through the lane, steadied when STAY ON THE FENCE came in some past the sixteenth pole and held second. BILLY JOE SHAVER bumped with the winner at the start, climbed early and trailed into the turn, angled out and spun five wide into the lane, came with a mild late bid and almost got up for second. STOLEN TREASURE brushed the gate but did not lose much at the start, raced up close four deep, put in a mild bid still wide on the turn and flattened out in the stretch run. JARAMA chased five deep to the stretch and never produced a bid. WHISKEY RYE bumped at the start, chased in the two path leaving the backstretch, steadied behind weakening rival and altered to the rail at the five-sixteenths pole, asked in the lane and could not rally. THIRSTY THURSDAY vied between rivals up the backstretch, could not kick on with the leaders around the bend and tired. BEAR COAST fought for the lead three deep, started to weaken around the turn and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOOK SMART sprinted to the front and showed the way up the backstretch, led along the rail through the turn, asked right handed with a furlong left to run, then widened under steady handling to win going away. DOUBLE JAB closest in pursuit two wide into the turn, gave chase along the rail into the stretch, moved out in the lane, could not make any headway on the winner in the drive but stayed on to best the rest. CRIBBAGE BOARD broke a step slow, chased from off the pace two wide then moved inside, ran into traffic past the quarter pole, lacked room again in upper stretch, moved out past the eight pole then steered towards the rail and summoned a mild rally for the show honors. RACHEL'S COACH chased on the inside into the turn, exited the bend a bit off the rail, moved out in the lane and could not rally. BARELY FUNTIONAL broke a step slow from outside, dropped back and angled in, saved ground through the turn, angled out and kept on to improve position. GEEZER tracked out of range early, rounded the bend two wide and failed to respond when asked. MEESH traveled outside a rival off the pace into the turn, spun three wide into the drive and failed to menace. GYPSY TEARS settled inside, cornered nicely into the stretch and failed to make an impact. GOLD COUNCIL traveled near the back early, rounded the bend two then three wide and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE CHOSEN VRON dueled outside PRINCIPE CARLO for command, shook free past the quarter pole, roused in upper stretch, tapped with the left hand midstretch and stayed clear under steady handling. BIG CITY LIGHTS stumbled leaving the gate, bumped inner rival shortly after and lost his path when THE CHOSEN VRON crossed in front, chased wide up the backstretch, ridden along six then five wide on the turn, finished determinedly down the lane but had to settle for second best. MOOSE MITCHELL raced up close outside the top pair early, rounded the bend five then four wide and weakened in the furlong grounds. NONE ABOVE THE LAW bumped with BIG CITY LIGHTS early, stalked off the inside, went three wide into the turn, steered to the rail around the bend, then faded in the drive. PRINCIPE CARLO dueled inside THE CHOSEN VRON to the turn, kept the pressure on to the quarter pole, could not kick on leaving the bend and tired in the lane.

A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden Races And Claiming Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered). (Rail at 18 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIVE ME THE LUTE chased between rivals then ran up on the heels of MAVEN and had to check at the seven-sixteenths pole, checked again entering the turn, raced along the inside then tipped out into the lane, ran into traffic at the eighth pole, steered to a clear path, surged late and edged MAVEN for the victory. MAVEN vied three deep then ceded command and chased outside a rival, rounded the bend two then three wide, rallied to the front with fifty yards remaining but run down by the winner in the final moments. HOT BOX vied for command inside rivals up the backstretch, dueled with outer rival past the five-sixteenths pole, inched ahead in upper stretch, put away CODE CHARLIE with a sixteenth remaining but offered no resistance to the top pair late and saved the show. KIMMER dropped back and angled to the inside, tipped out into the drive but got put in tight between rivals in upper stretch, moved inward and put in a late rally but missed the show. PERFECTIONISTIC broke out and bumped, chased three deep then two wide into the turn, bothered by MAVEN coming out slightly midway around the bend, spun four wide into the lane and needed to find more in the late stages. LANSDOWNE (GB) bumped by PERFECTIONISTIC in the beginning, chased four then three deep up the backstretch, exited the bend five wide, moved out in the lane and failed to threaten. TOM BOMBADIL raced in range along the inside, hugged the rail to the stretch and lacked a response when called upon. STORMY SAMURAI vied between rivals early, fought between to the five-sixteenths pole then failed to kick on with the top pair, chased two wide into the drive and flattened out. CODE CHARLIE vied four then three deep early, continued to battle three wide then dueled outside HOT BOX past the five-sixteenths pole, fought into the furlong grounds then gave way late.
